<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7492ed82-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s140510"><num value="140510">§ 140510.</num><heading> Service of process</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The corporation shall have a designated agent in the District of Columbia to receive service of process for the corporation. Notice to or service on the agent, or mailed to the business address of the agent, is notice to or service on the corporation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7492ed83-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1384">112 Stat. 1384</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
